title: Google\Cloud\Dataproc\V1\LifecycleConfig
name: LifecycleConfig
description:
Specifies the cluster auto-delete schedule configuration.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dataproc.v1.LifecycleConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.idle_delete_ttl
params.description: Optional. The duration to keep the cluster alive while idling (when no jobs are running). Passing this threshold will cause the cluster to be deleted. Minimum value is 10 minutes; maximum value is 14 days (see JSON representation of Duration.

params.name: data.auto_delete_time
params.description: Optional. The time when cluster will be auto-deleted (see JSON representation of Timestamp).

params.name: data.auto_delete_ttl
params.description: Optional. The lifetime duration of cluster. The cluster will be auto-deleted at the end of this period. Minimum value is 10 minutes; maximum value is 14 days (see JSON representation of Duration).

params.name: data.idle_start_time
params.description: Output only. The time when cluster became idle (most recent job finished) and became eligible for deletion due to idleness (see JSON representation of Timestamp).
